  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="body:1;5:9">
    <section id="about" class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="section:1;6:25"><title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="title:2;6:32">Helion OpenStack 2.0 Installation</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="p:1;7:10">Beginning with HP Helion OpenStack 2.0 Beta 2, you have two options for installing your
        cloud. You can use a GUI that runs in your web browser or you can install via a CLI that
        exposes the full power and flexibility of HP Helion OpenStack 2.0.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="section:2;11:14">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="p:2;12:10">You should use the GUI if: 
        <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="ul:1;13:13">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:1;14:13">You are installing a simple demo or proof-of-concept cloud. </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:2;15:13">You have less than about 15 nodes (it will work for larger numbers but entering all that
          data in the GUI will get tiresome). </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:3;17:13">You are not planning to deploy availability zones or use L3 segmentation in your initial
          deployment. </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:4;19:13">You are happy with the tuned HP default OpenStack configuration.</li>
      </ul>
        </p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="p:3;22:10">Instructions for installing via the GUI are here.</p> 
    </section>
    <ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="ul:2;24:9">
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:5;25:11"><xref href="gui_installer.dita#install_gui" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="xref:1;25:55" type="topic"><?ditaot usertext?>Installing via the GUI</xref></li>
    </ul>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="section:3;27:14">Note that reconfiguration of your cloud, at the moment, is done via the CLI. The GUI
      installer is for first-time installation. </section>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="section:4;29:14">You should use the CLI if: <ul id="ul_wbl_2lw_kt" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="ul:3;29:64">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:6;30:13">You are installing a more complex or large-scale cloud. </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:7;31:13">You have more than about 15 nodes. </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:8;32:13">You need to use availability zones or the server groups functionality of the cloud
          model. See the <xref href="input_model.dita#input_model" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="xref:2;33:68" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?>Input Model page</xref> for more
          information. </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:9;35:13">You want to customize the cloud configuration beyond the tuned defaults that HP provides
          out of the box. </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\installation_overview.dita" xtrc="li:10;37:13">You need deeper customizations than are possible to express using the GUI.</li>
      </ul> Instructions for installing via the CLI are here</section>
